  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3779" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>7 Getaria, San Sebastian. 9 May 1900. </dateline>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> H. Schuchardt, </opener>
        <p>I have received your assurances that you feel no <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">
groll</hi> towards me, <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">and you certainly have no right to feel any towards a would-be friend. </hi>But your behaviour about my brochure offered to, &amp; finally accepted by, your University, and all that you have written to or about me for three years past, <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">shews that I cannot count you among my friends</hi>. I <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">regret it very deeply</hi>, and only hope that you may repent <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">&amp; change your mind</hi>. METANOIA! Some Basque students would be glad to know when, &amp; where, &amp; at what price, your edition of Leiçarragas new Testament is to appear. I am unable to give any information on the subject, though I was the first to announce your project in a newspaper in Basqueland some years ago. I never received any <hi
            rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">prospectus</hi> of the edition. Of course I wish to promote its sale, &amp; prepare the road for a good reception for it, even though I expect to find some small reasons for disagreeing with your manner of presenting the text to the public. You told me at Munich that Axular was the only Basque <hi
            rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">classic</hi>. I think Mendiburus book of 1747 is equal to it, though it does not quote classic authors. My edition of this will be on sale in a few days. A copy on superior paper, post free registered, shall be sent to you, if you let me have <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">here</hi> a post office order, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">payable at Biarritz</hi> to the value of 5 marks.</p>
        <closer>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
